FBIS4-59777 "drnes096_l_94011" FBIS-NES-94-096 Daily Report 17 May 1994 ISRAEL Cabinet Briefed on PLO, Palestinian Authority Cabinet Briefed on PLO, Palestinian Authority TA1705162794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 17 May 94 TA1705162794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] The PLO leadership has ordered that guns held by Palestinians in Gaza be collected, but only few heeded this order. This was reported at the cabinet's weekly session today. Our correspondent Shlomo Raz reports that the ministers were also told that Fatah activists in the Gaza Strip have been criticizing the PLO leadership, claiming that it disregards them. The cabinet was further told that Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] has been questioning the legitimacy of the PLO leadership and opposing the agreement. There is a fear that the economic deterioration in Gaza might be followed by a security deterioration. The ministers were also told that the Palestinian Authority will take part in issuing working permits in Israel for Palestinian laborers.
